<div class="mbxxl">
    <div class="mod">
        <div class="inner">
            <div class="bd">
                <p>Highly customizable grid system used on all FINN pages. combine <code>.line</code> and multiple <code>.unit</code> to build complex responsive grids. There are several ways of controlling responsivness and also how many units you get pr line. (Think of line more like a containing block, sometimes its a line, sometimes elements may stack differently).</p>
                <div class="r-margin">
                  <table class="outerborder">
                      <thead>
                          <tr>
                              <th>Property</th>
                              <th>Description</th>
                          </tr>
                      </thead>
                      <tbody>
                          <tr>
                              <th scope="row"><code>.line</code></th>
                              <td>Groups units on one horizontal line. Note: for mobile layout units may be stacked to avoid horizontal scrolling.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                              <th scope="row"><code>.unit</code></th>
                              <td>Base class which divides a line into sections (columns).</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                              <th scope="row"><code>.sizeXofY</code></th>
                              <td>Extends <code>unit</code>. Indicates the fractional width of the unit, for example <code>size3of4</code> would take
                                    up three quarters, or 75%, of the horizontal space.

                                    <h5 class="mln">Supported fractions:</h5>
                                    <ul class="man horizontal-list">
                                        <li class="phm">1</li>
                                        <li class="phm">1/2</li>
                                        <li class="phm">1/3</li>
                                        <li class="phm">2/3</li>
                                        <li class="phm">1/4</li>
                                        <li class="phm">3/4</li>
                                        <li class="phm">1/5</li>
                                        <li class="phm">2/5</li>
                                        <li class="phm">3/5</li>
                                        <li class="phm">4/5</li>
                                        <li class="phm">1/6</li>
                                        <li class="phm">5/6</li>
                                    </ul>
                                <p class="strong">
                                    Intended use: Non-responsive liquid elements
                                </p>
                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                              <th scope="row"><code class="no-break">.r-sizeXofY</code></th>
                              <td>Extends <code>unit</code>. Indicates the number of grid units this element spans, for example <code>r-size2of3</code>
                                  would take up 2 of 3 columns. Collapses to 1 column at 768px.
                                  <p class="strong">Intended use: Column based contents</p>
                                </td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                              <th scope="row"><code>.r-colsXtoY</code></th>
                              <td>Extends <code>line</code>. Responsive column setup for content. Classname indicates number of colums, for example
                                  <code>r-cols2to4</code> will fit 2 columns on mobile screens and 4 columns from 768px and up.
                                  <p class="mhn">Great for dynamic content when you dont know how many units youll get.</p>

                                  <p class="mhn">Supported combos: 1to2, 1to3, 1to4, 2to3, 2to4, 2to5, 2to6</p>

                              <p class="strong">Intended use: Column based contents
                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                              <th scope="row"><code>.colsXupto[Breakpoint]</code></th>
                              <td>
                                  <p class="mhn mtn">Extends <code>line</code>.
                                  <p class="mhn">Classname indicates number of colums at specific breakpoints, for example <code>.cols1upto480 .cols2upto768 .cols4from990</code> will fit 1 column below 480px, 2 columns between 480px and 767px, and 4 columns from 990px to infinity</p>
                                  <p class="red mhn">! Works in conjunction with colsXfrom990, remember to set this aswell, or 990px+ will get whatever is default (usually 1col )</p>
                                  <p class="mhn"><code>.cols[X]upto[breakpoint]</code> Sets number of columns up to specified breakpoint</p>
                                  <p class="mhn"><code>.cols[X]from990</code> Sets number of columns from 990 and up</p>
                                  <p class="mhn">Supported column count: 1 - 8</p>
                                  <p class="mhn">Supported breakpoints: 480px, 640px, 768px, 990px</p>
                                  <p class="strong">Intended use: Column based contents where we need more control</p>
                            </td>
                          </tr>
                      </tbody>
                  </table>
                </div>

